Focus:
1. Be especially concrete about execution support for downstream project agents, not only framework philosophy.
2. Assume the repository already has strong design/governance surfaces for anti-drift, receipts, sync audit, discussion packets, git audit, SKILL governance, and strict adoption guidance.
3. Identify which missing execution-layer tools, wrappers, validators, review loops, schedulers, or artifact-generation surfaces should be added next.
4. Pay extra attention to how downstream repositories can prove they adopted the framework honestly and can execute it with enough tool support.
5. Prefer proposals that make downstream failure states auditable instead of relying on agent goodwill.

